<section class="py-20 bg-gray-50">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-4xl">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
        What makes it
        <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-600 to-red-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent">different</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600">
        A few key differences from the stock sound menu.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 p-6 bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-orange-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-1">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="m9 9 10.5-3m0 6.553v3.75a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-1.632 2.163l-1.32.377a1.803 1.803 0 1 1-.99-3.467l2.31-.66a2.25 2.25 0 0 0 1.632-2.163Zm0 0V2.25L9 5.25v10.303m0 0v3.75a2.25 2.25 0 0 1-1.632 2.163l-1.32.377a1.803 1.803 0 0 1-.99-3.467l2.31-.66A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 9 15.553Z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Separate Music volume</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-600">The stock menu only controls overall Mac volume. Menu Volume gives you a <strong>second slider just for Apple Music</strong> — not available in the stock menu.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 p-6 bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-orange-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-1">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10.5 6h9.75M10.5 6a1.5 1.5 0 1 1-3 0m3 0a1.5 1.5 0 1 0-3 0M3.75 6H7.5m3 12h9.75m-9.75 0a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-3 0m3 0a1.5 1.5 0 0 0-3 0m-3.75 0H7.5m9-6h3.75m-3.75 0a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-3 0m3 0a1.5 1.5 0 0 0-3 0m-9.75 0h9.75" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Always visible sliders</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-600">See both volume levels at a glance. The stock menu hides the slider until you click — ours shows current levels instantly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex items-start space-x-4 p-6 bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-orange-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-1">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-orange-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3.75 13.5l10.5-11.25L12 10.5h8.25L9.75 21.75 12 13.5H3.75z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Designed for music listeners</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-600">Control both volumes separately—adjust either one without affecting the other.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>